Critical thinking

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I really enjoyed the helpful note taking packets provided by Professor Su Ji.

Strengths: well paced, high quality instructor (Su Ji), flexible time given for doing assignments 
Weaknesses: none
To me, the strength is accessibility into resources. I dont believe there are any particular weaknesses.
Had opportunity to ask questions through pre class activities  and felt like welcoming space
The workshop material was way too difficult and felt like a waste of time due to how hard it was

Being taught by Su Ji was amazing. From the first class she set a very chill atmosphere that made it possible for me to engage with her s my professor without fear and also engage with the other course mates.  The structure of the class was also amazing: using worksheets to actually work through problems in class, using examples that are like a reflection of how exams are set and the PSETs, Concept checks and workshops to expose you to the more application side of Calculus improved my critical thinking. The extended deadlines on PSETs was also a huge lifesaver sometimes.
I think the course was very beginner friendly however I found the order of some of the topics to be disorganizing.
Sometimes the discussion section was not super beneficial, but I felt the teaching was very interactive and helped make me a better student
My strengths were the different concepts we learned and applying different things. However, my weaknesses were memorizing equations and limit definition algebra.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: No, unless you need it for your major. A hard QR credit. There are easier ones out there.
Yes, I would. It is challenging, but engaging.

Yes
It's a really good beginner class to start and learn Calculus. The instructor-student ratio is favorable to keep up with the class and catch up with concepts you couldn't fully understand in class
Yes
Yes. It is a very good foundational course if you have little or no background in Calculus.
I would because my instructor was very friendly and dedicated lots of her time to teaching us students
Yes! Nice QR credit with great professors
No I would not, I would recommend to do MATH 112 because they do the same thing and it is only one semester.
